OKAY, so I thought I was doing okay with handling the whole "depression" thing, if you want to call it that, but then I keep thinking, I have no one to talk to, like no one who's really there for me, and that sucks because I can't like keep everything in all the time. Like i have Caitlin, who I can pick up a conversation with at any moment, but it's not the same because she's not here. And Lexi, I have her too, but there's not much to talk about. Like, I just wish it was last year again, it was so much better. And I think I'm going to call Caitlin and Lexi tonight, and see if they want to do something this weekend. I miss them too much. They've always been there for me, and they would never not be there for me, I know it for a fact, and I just wish there were people like that here at sem, I'm sure there are, but I'm having such a hard time finding them. IF YOU'RE A GOOD PERSON AND YOU WANNA BE MY BESTEST FRIEND FOREVER AND EVER, COME FIND ME!!  :(


Please comment me with my best qualities, to cheer me up, they can be annonmous, or with your name. ♥

I haven't updated in a while! Anyways, let's see what's been going on. Tuesday, I think tuesday, I went to Sarah's to sleep over. It was me, hovel, carolyn, emily, lauren, and michele. We had fun! We went sledding and got yelled at by some guy who told us the park was closed, I definatly told him that I was deaf and he was being predjudice for not using sign language, of course I had to translate to him with my hands. Stupid Hicks. Anyways then we watched Thirteen, scariest movie I've ever seen, I'm so freaked out now. I swear it didn't influence me..NOT. Then in the morning me, hovel, carolyn and emily went skiing. It was my first time ever going skiing! I was really bad. They took me on the "main hill" which I like to call "Never go on if it's your first day skiing, you're better off on the bunny hill" and well, let's just say I ran into a tree, got fed up, and def. walked halfway down the hill.

But anyways, I'm not excited for Christmas at all. It's really weird, like I haven't even wrapped presents yet, and I refused to put any ornaments on the tree, because it's a fake tree, and I only like the real ones. :]  I know, I'm such a brat. Anyways, break has been amazing..not.


I've been having spaz attacks A LOT lately, like I've been flipping out on people non-stop. I think the whole depression things coming back. Speaking of that, Sarah I'm sorry I made you like..die. :(  I love you! Sorry!!

COMMENT ME ♥

I'm seeing this entry as being somewhat long, so I'll make it in sections!


KiSSMAS BASH 2004- Wow! This was by far the most amazing concert I've ever been to in my whole entire life! I can't even like explain half of it, because I'm still in such shock! So, I'll start from the very beginning.

I went to Carolyn's aunt's house with her and Sarah because we were getting ready there with everyone later. So, we got there, and her mom had to go get some stuff so we were just hanging out. Carolyn took a shower and practically flashed us..it was bad! Sarah washed her hair in the sink while I was sitting on her back trying to see how long I could balance. Anyways, we got ready then Emma came over, then Abi, Zoe, Allie, Michele, Lauren, and finally Emily. We ate pizza and dolled-up even more and then we left.

We had seats in the 300s level ($17 tickets..LMAO) So of course, we went seat hopping! We got kicked out of a few rows, but finally Emily found her Ski friend, Lindsay, and we sat with her because she -for some reandom reason- had like 10 extra tickets..but anyways we were FOURTH ROW! AND WE WERE RIGHT NEXT TO BACK STAGE! WE GOT ALL THESE AUTOGRAPHS IT WAS AMAZING!!

SWITCHFOOT- My favorite band of all times..okay, they got out there and I was like bawling because I was so excited to see them, I couldn't believe I was actually seeing them, I was about to die of happiness. It was bad. Then Sarah got to go back stage to see them with her OP friends, and I made her hug my fav. guy for me. Ahhhhh..and then he ran into the aud. and I like touched him..ahhhhhhh....

GAVIN DEGRAW, GOOD CHARLOTTE, SIMPLE PLAN, AVRIL LAVIGNE, JOJO, 7 DAY FAITH, SKY SWEEDNAM, SWITCHFOOT AND VANESSA CARLTON WERE AMAZING!
So anywways, The concert was amazing for our measly $17


Then we went back to Emma's and we slept over. I love how you can totally be 100% NOT (I repeat, NOT) a lesbian and if you're at a school with all girls you can't get out of spooning. It's bad guys. Spooning wars. Wow. What fun times, it was amazing, and we had a great time. BAHh..ERRKHAHHA. Sarah and Carolyn Raped me like 20 times, it was sooooo bad, and Sarah had a massive obsession with my belly-button because it's an outie. Heehee.


So anyways, that was my amazing Friday, I know you're all jealous,..you know you love me mucho!


♥ COMMENT IF YOU LOVE ME..

Well, I'm doing much better in school! I am so proud of myself, I'm not failing anything anymore, and I actually have A's and B's in most classes! I am so proud of myself, you have no idea! I've been working so hard! I'm about to make a picturetrail thing so I can post the pictures I just got!

I'll always remember that late afternoon...


*TEAR*

Well. Let me see. Gym was crazy! I was extra beastly, I don't think I ever worked that hard in gym at Heim, but I guess it's different when you are at an all girls school, and no one cares if you get sweaty..Rachel had a shadow today, and then she threw-up so she went home, I kind of felt bad for her shadow! Then Sarah had a shadow, and Sarah being the massive druggie we know she is, drugged her shadow with candy! What she was thinking, I don't know, but her shadow was, let's say "extra perky" from then on. Ay. Then me and Sarah were suppost to both "get the flu/a cold" tomorrow so we didn't have to go to school, but that didn't work out too well, because I actually DO feel sick, and I'm going to go to school tomorrow anyways, because I'd feel way too guilty! So, that's that. The Canisus dance was better than the other ones, I personally thought, except for the lack of guys. I danced with a lot of the guys though, which is weird, I think it's the fact that my braces were off :) but most of my friends didn't have fun because they didn't dance with a lot of guys, but it's usually me without the guys, and them with the guys, so I kind of had my glory moment! Let's see, what else has been going on? I hear rumors are being spread about me randomly in North. Good riddance, they can say whatever they want about me, because, thank god I don't have to put up with thouse people anymore! I'm almost out of proctored, and I'm so excited! I've been working really hard, and it's finally working out! FREE PERIODS HERE I COME! We're doing this complete BS report in Physics ans Spanish where we have to pick a topic related to Physics, and do the poster and present it in Spanish, or French. HOW RETARDED IS THAT!? Just be happy you don't have to do it (unless you're a freshman at sem). So, that's pretty much it, except the fact that I have to have to responsibility for doing secret santas for my group, and I've never done those before, we're getting out of hand of people though, we might as well have to whole freshman class do it, but I just can't say no to people who ask me if they can be included! Carolyn, on the other hand, has NO PROBLEM saying "No" to people. Poor Ellen, her grandpa died, and I FELT HORRIBLE! Whatcha gonna do though? All you can do is say your sorry. I feel terrible. Well, this has been WAY too long, and I have a lot more homework to do, and my arms are killing! LOL! Leave some love!

♥
